♫ <i>Listen to the rain falling into the silent forest</i> ♫

39
00:04:49,870 --> 00:04:55,110
Nan Nan.

40
00:04:59,490 --> 00:05:01,570
Nan Nan.

41
00:05:04,020 --> 00:05:09,420
♫ <i>The world is like a quiet island</i> ♫

42
00:05:12,380 --> 00:05:17,480
♫ <i>The sky is turning bright without a sound</i> ♫

43
00:05:19,720 --> 00:05:24,520
♫ <i>Waiting for the seabirds to call forth the ripples</i> ♫

44
00:05:27,100 --> 00:05:33,300
♫ <i>Waiting for a ray of sunlight to shine across
the lake into my heart</i> ♫

45
00:05:34,170 --> 00:05:35,860
<i>Hongdou!</i>

46
00:05:36,490 --> 00:05:39,900
<i>The wind really blows from all directions.</i>

47
00:05:39,900 --> 00:05:41,930
<i>It's so wild.</i>

48
00:05:41,930 --> 00:05:48,480
♫ <i>The reflection of clouds, the changing moon,
and the starry sky</i> ♫

49
00:05:48,480 --> 00:05:54,320
♫ <i>Disoriented footsteps will gradually be erased</i> ♫

50
00:05:56,500 --> 00:05:58,710
♫ <i>The light and shadows of the seasons</i> ♫

51
00:05:58,710 --> 00:06:03,140
♫ <i> I've seen the meteor that lights up the night sky</i> ♫

52
00:06:03,140 --> 00:06:08,760
♫ <i>When the wind rises, the sky will be cloudless</i> ♫

53
00:06:12,730 --> 00:06:15,230
<i>Cutie Pie ate it!</i>

54
00:06:15,230 --> 00:06:17,490
Cutie Pie, this cucumber is very yummy.

55
00:06:17,490 --> 00:06:19,850
Cutie Pie, this spicy bar is amazing.

56
00:06:19,850 --> 00:06:21,530
There's chocolate, too.

57
00:06:21,530 --> 00:06:24,860
I really pity Cutie Pie. There are so many yummy things around.

58
00:06:24,860 --> 00:06:27,930
Uncle A'Yao only feeds it grass.

59
00:06:27,930 --> 00:06:30,490
He's horrible.

60
00:06:31,760 --> 00:06:34,170
Why am I horrible?

61
00:06:35,400 --> 00:06:37,210
What are you feeding Cutie Pie?

62
00:06:37,210 --> 00:06:39,730
- Run!
- Help!

63
00:06:39,730 --> 00:06:41,520
- Got one.
- Leave me!

64
00:06:41,520 --> 00:06:44,670
I won't die! Run! Hurry up!

65
00:06:44,670 --> 00:06:48,070
Run! Run!!!

66
00:06:48,840 --> 00:06:51,370
Apples are okay. Cucumbers are also okay.

67
00:06:51,370 --> 00:06:53,430
However, you can't feed it spicy bars or chocolate.

68
00:06:53,430 --> 00:06:56,340
Cutie Pie will get a stomach ache if it eats these, got it?

69
00:06:56,340 --> 00:07:00,620
I fed it roasted eggplants, and it ate that.

70
00:07:02,520 --> 00:07:05,370
When was that?

71
00:07:09,950 --> 00:07:14,560
Uncle A'Yao's rice noodles are so yummy, right?

72
00:07:14,560 --> 00:07:15,590
It's tasy!

73
00:07:15,590 --> 00:07:18,440
Super yummy!

74
00:07:27,170 --> 00:07:28,250
Yeah!

75
00:07:28,250 --> 00:07:30,050
So tasty.

76
00:07:31,700 --> 00:07:35,340
<i>[Wind]</i>

77
00:07:39,590 --> 00:07:41,200
- Na Na.
- What's up?

78
00:07:41,200 --> 00:07:43,180
It isn't crowded today.

79
00:07:43,180 --> 00:07:45,470
Why did you ask me to be a volunteer here?

80
00:07:45,470 --> 00:07:47,540
I'm a guest.

81
00:07:48,240 --> 00:07:52,910
Hongdou, you'll be bored if you don't do anything.

82
00:07:52,910 --> 00:07:56,590
How about volunteering for me? I'll cover your meals.

83
00:07:58,200 --> 00:08:01,080
I'm not bored. I'm here to rest.

84
00:08:01,080 --> 00:08:02,660
I'm reading now.

85
00:08:02,660 --> 00:08:06,840
I saw that. You read briefly and then started using your phone.

86
00:08:06,840 --> 00:08:10,990
You read the headline news and got into a bad mood, right?

87
00:08:10,990 --> 00:08:15,210
Are you really planning to wander around for three full months?

88
00:08:15,210 --> 00:08:17,140
I'm not wandering around.

89
00:08:17,140 --> 00:08:19,590
I'm either sitting or lying down.

90
00:08:19,590 --> 00:08:22,660
Who was the one who said exercise promises longevity?

91
00:08:22,660 --> 00:08:26,600
Exercise promises longevity, but not work.

92
00:08:26,600 --> 00:08:29,010
Volunteering is also a form of rest.

93
00:08:29,010 --> 00:08:30,610
That's different.

94
00:08:30,610 --> 00:08:34,180
Volunteering is free labor.

95
00:08:34,180 --> 00:08:37,580
Labor and rest are two separate things.

96
00:08:37,580 --> 00:08:41,430
Don't trick me with capitalist wordplay.

97
00:08:42,560 --> 00:08:44,830
Can't Xiaochun find another worker?

98
00:08:44,830 --> 00:08:48,710
We have enough workers in the cafe. There's me, Granny Xiuying, and Granny Caiyun.

99
00:08:48,710 --> 00:08:52,600
Xiaochun drops by to help out when she's done with her work.

100
00:08:53,580 --> 00:08:56,330
The grannies are mascots.

101
00:08:57,970 --> 00:09:01,530
They're the faces of our cafe.

102
00:09:01,530 --> 00:09:03,860
A volunteer just needs to help out when it's busy.

103
00:09:03,860 --> 00:09:06,910
You'll have your free time.

104
00:09:06,910 --> 00:09:10,040
Why are you coaxing me to be a volunteer?

105
00:09:11,030 --> 00:09:14,240
It's just... a casual question.

106
00:09:19,210 --> 00:09:20,750
- What's wrong?
- Hongdou.

107
00:09:20,750 --> 00:09:22,740
Did that customer leave?

108
00:09:22,740 --> 00:09:24,730
Yeah, quite some time ago.

109
00:09:28,800 --> 00:09:32,380
Another forgotten bill. It happens once or twice a month.

110
00:09:32,380 --> 00:09:33,860
Let me take a look.

111
00:09:39,270 --> 00:09:40,860
I'll chase after them.

112
00:09:40,860 --> 00:09:43,730
- Where are you going?
- The town entrance.

113
00:09:47,520 --> 00:09:49,200
That's Sister Hongdou.

114
00:09:49,200 --> 00:09:52,170
- She's running so fast.
- What's she doing?

115
00:09:52,170 --> 00:09:53,600
I don't know. Go after her.

116
00:09:53,600 --> 00:09:55,090
After her!

117
00:09:55,580 --> 00:10:00,140
♫ <i>Merrily visiting the homeland of the Bai people</i> ♫

118
00:10:00,140 --> 00:10:03,780
♫ <i>The Bai people are happy to welcome them with Bai wine</i> ♫

119
00:10:03,780 --> 00:10:05,830
It's Xiao Hu Lu and the rest.

120
00:10:05,830 --> 00:10:08,280
- They're chasing that aunty.
- After them!

121
00:10:08,280 --> 00:10:11,600
♫ <i>The first toast for health</i> ♫

122
00:10:11,600 --> 00:10:15,700
♫ <i>The second toast for a smooth career</i> ♫

123
00:10:16,800 --> 00:10:20,100
♫ <i>The third toast for friendship</i> ♫

124
00:10:20,100 --> 00:10:22,330
Excuse me, wait a minute!

125
00:10:26,300 --> 00:10:28,650
- What's the matter?
- You forgot to pay the bill.

126
00:10:28,650 --> 00:10:31,000
- Didn't you pay the bill?
- I forgot about it.

127
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:32,570
Sorry about that. How much is it?

128
00:10:32,570 --> 00:10:34,260
- ¥207.
- Okay.

129
00:10:34,260 --> 00:10:36,070
Scan this.

130
00:10:45,040 --> 00:10:46,720
All done.

131
00:10:50,160 --> 00:10:51,750
Why are you chasing me?

132
00:10:51,760 --> 00:10:54,210
Sister Hongdou, how can you run so fast?

133
00:10:54,210 --> 00:10:57,570
I've never seen you run so fast before.

134
00:10:59,230 --> 00:11:01,680
I'm dead tired.

135
00:11:01,680 --> 00:11:03,650
- Xu Hongdou.
- Don't run so fast next time.

136
00:11:03,650 --> 00:11:05,540
Sister Hongdou.

137
00:11:10,760 --> 00:11:12,750
Come on, there's enough for everyone. Don't worry.

138
00:11:12,750 --> 00:11:14,600
Uncle, I want a cream one.

139
00:11:14,600 --> 00:11:17,140
Cream? Okay. Who hasn't taken one?

140
00:11:17,140 --> 00:11:18,680
Everyone gets one.

141
00:11:18,680 --> 00:11:20,090
- Who else? Here you go.
- Thanks, Uncle.

142
00:11:20,090 --> 00:11:22,480
- Thank you, Uncle A'Yao.
- One per person.

143
00:11:22,480 --> 00:11:26,030
Everyone got one, right? Go back home now.

144
00:11:26,030 --> 00:11:29,040
- Stay safe.
- Goodbye, Granny.
- Bye.

145
00:11:29,040 --> 00:11:30,850
Be careful when crossing the road. Okay?

146
00:11:30,850 --> 00:11:31,880
Goodbye, Granny.

147
00:11:31,880 --> 00:11:33,090
Goodbye.

148
00:11:33,090 --> 00:11:34,680
- Goodbye, Granny.
- Goodbye.

149
00:11:34,680 --> 00:11:38,380
- Goodbye, Granny.
- Okay, don't rush.

150
00:11:38,380 --> 00:11:40,570
Granny, have some jujube juice.

151
00:11:40,610 --> 00:11:42,630
- For you, too.
- Thank you.

152
00:11:43,600 --> 00:11:45,000
You're pretty impressive.

153
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:47,600
This place is filled with streets and alleys, but you've nailed them.

154
00:11:47,600 --> 00:11:50,000
They had tons of bags with them,

155
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:53,400
so I guessed they'd flag for a taxi at the town entrance.

156
00:11:53,400 --> 00:11:56,600
It's the experience of a 10-year veteran in the service industry.

157
00:11:56,600 --> 00:12:00,300
The worst that could happen in the cafe is customers forgetting to pay the bill.

158
00:12:00,300 --> 00:12:05,600
The hotel industry has far more complex problems.

159
00:12:08,800 --> 00:12:10,700
Granny, let me do it.

160
00:12:10,700 --> 00:12:12,300
Leave this to me.

161
00:12:16,200 --> 00:12:17,600
Do you still feel warm?

162
00:12:21,000 --> 00:12:22,300
Is this delicious?

163
00:12:22,300 --> 00:12:23,600
I'll give you another one if it isn't nice.

164
00:12:23,600 --> 00:12:25,600
How about watermelon juice? Lemon juice?

165
00:12:25,600 --> 00:12:26,900
Apple juice?

166
00:12:28,100 --> 00:12:29,300
It's fine.

167
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:33,200
How about we have a barbecue party tomorrow night?

168
00:12:33,200 --> 00:12:36,000
You've been here for days, but we haven't had a party.

169
00:12:36,800 --> 00:12:37,900
How's that?

170
00:12:39,200 --> 00:12:42,900
We can't make a commotion after 8:30 p.m., right?

171
00:12:42,900 --> 00:12:44,700
Won't we be a nuisance to the neighbors?

172
00:12:44,700 --> 00:12:46,900
It's fine. I won't be annoyed.

173
00:12:46,900 --> 00:12:50,300
Youngsters having a party isn't a nuisance.

174
00:12:50,300 --> 00:12:52,500
It's settled then.

175
00:12:52,500 --> 00:12:53,800
Sure.

176
00:12:58,300 --> 00:13:00,400
- Aunty!
- A'Yao.

177
00:13:00,400 --> 00:13:01,700
- Uncle, are you done for the day?
- Yes.

178
00:13:01,700 --> 00:13:02,900
Okay.

179
00:13:02,900 --> 00:13:04,800
- Please take care of my granny.
- Sure.

180
00:13:04,800 --> 00:13:06,200
We're heading to the horse ranch for a meeting.

181
00:13:06,200 --> 00:13:07,000
Okay, bye-bye.

182
00:13:07,000 --> 00:13:08,000
- Go on.
- Bye-bye.

183
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:09,400
- Let's go.
- Bye, Aunty.

184
00:13:09,400 --> 00:13:10,800
Come on.

185
00:13:18,400 --> 00:13:19,800
Granny.

186
00:13:20,700 --> 00:13:23,200
Did A'Yao fall in love with me?

187
00:13:26,000 --> 00:13:27,200
I'm just kidding.

188
00:13:27,200 --> 00:13:28,500
It's a joke.

189
00:13:28,500 --> 00:13:29,900
Just a joke.

190
00:13:44,300 --> 00:13:46,600
Why isn't Xia Xia home yet?

191
00:13:46,600 --> 00:13:47,600
He should be here soon.

192
00:13:47,600 --> 00:13:50,200
He got off the plane too late last night, so he went to A'Yuan's place.

193
00:13:50,200 --> 00:13:53,400
They'll come back together this morning.

194
00:13:53,400 --> 00:13:55,700
A'Yuan is such a handful...

195
00:13:57,700 --> 00:13:59,400
- Eat your eggs.
- Okay.

196
00:14:03,200 --> 00:14:04,500
Is he back?

197
00:14:05,400 --> 00:14:07,900
- You're back!
- Mom.

198
00:14:07,900 --> 00:14:10,200
Uncle, what yummy food did you bring back for me?

199
00:14:10,200 --> 00:14:12,700
Only food is on your mind.

200
00:14:12,700 --> 00:14:14,700
You bought so many things.

201
00:14:14,700 --> 00:14:16,200
Sister.

202
00:14:16,800 --> 00:14:19,100
Put your stuff down and eat first.

203
00:14:20,500 --> 00:14:21,800
Uncle, what's this?

204
00:14:21,800 --> 00:14:24,100
Palmier. You can have it as a snack.

205
00:14:27,800 --> 00:14:31,300
You have to finish your meal first. Snacks come after your meal.

206
00:14:31,300 --> 00:14:33,600
Just let her eat it if she wants to.

207
00:14:33,600 --> 00:14:36,700
Hu Lu, get your uncle's utensils.

208
00:14:41,200 --> 00:14:45,600
Xia Xia, I thought you said you were applying for a job in a studio in Shanghai?

209
00:14:45,600 --> 00:14:47,400
- Did you go there?
- I did.

210
00:14:47,400 --> 00:14:49,000
They said I'm not suited for the job.

211
00:14:49,000 --> 00:14:50,500
I have to improve my skills.

212
00:14:50,500 --> 00:14:52,200
Weren't they particular about your educational background?

213
00:14:52,200 --> 00:14:53,700
Nope.

214
00:14:53,700 --> 00:14:55,800
I'll work even harder under Master's guidance.

215
00:14:55,800 --> 00:14:57,700
That's right. You're a rookie.

216
00:14:57,700 --> 00:15:01,100
Be diligent in your learning.

217
00:15:01,700 --> 00:15:05,200
You're pretty optimistic. With his temper, who knows if he'll take you back?

218
00:15:05,200 --> 00:15:07,000
Why not?

219
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:09,000
I'll beg him until he agrees.

220
00:15:10,600 --> 00:15:14,100
Oh my god. It's way too crispy.

221
00:15:15,800 --> 00:15:17,100
Xie Xiaoxia.

222
00:15:17,100 --> 00:15:20,200
She learned all these from those short clips you showed her.

223
00:15:20,200 --> 00:15:21,800
What the heck is that?

224
00:15:21,800 --> 00:15:23,900
I didn't let her watch anything. Don't blame me for it.

225
00:15:23,900 --> 00:15:25,600
Here, have some meat sauce.

226
00:15:25,600 --> 00:15:27,200
Is Uncle's souvenir tasty?

227
00:15:27,200 --> 00:15:29,000
- Take this yourself.
- Okay.

228
00:15:31,400 --> 00:15:34,000
You sure treat your son well.

229
00:15:40,600 --> 00:15:42,600
Granny, leave it. I'll do it.

230
00:15:42,600 --> 00:15:44,000
I can cook.

231
00:15:44,000 --> 00:15:47,200
A'Yuan likes my cooking.

232
00:15:47,200 --> 00:15:48,700
Add two more.

233
00:15:49,600 --> 00:15:52,200
He's the only one who wants steamed eggs. Both of us eat fried eggs.

234
00:15:52,200 --> 00:15:53,700
Why are you making two different types of eggs?

235
00:15:53,700 --> 00:15:55,500
All you do is spoil him.

236
00:15:55,500 --> 00:15:57,400
He doesn't like egg yolks.

237
00:15:57,400 --> 00:15:59,000
He's trying to build up his body.

238
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:00,600
He wants to build up his body?

239
00:16:00,600 --> 00:16:03,500
If he grows any taller, he'll be shooting through our roof.

240
00:16:03,500 --> 00:16:05,800
You're biased.

241
00:16:05,800 --> 00:16:08,200
You're so old, but look at his age.

242
00:16:08,200 --> 00:16:11,000
When I was his age, you didn't spoil me in the slightest.

243
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:14,400
You chased me around the village and beat me.

244
00:16:14,400 --> 00:16:16,000
Every time I tried to spank you, you would flee.

245
00:16:16,000 --> 00:16:17,600
You probably didn't get hit much.

246
00:16:17,600 --> 00:16:20,100
Anyway, you're playing favorites to your grandson.

247
00:16:20,100 --> 00:16:23,400
Enough. Give me the dark soy sauce.

248
00:16:36,600 --> 00:16:38,300
When you need to add the salt, let me do it.

249
00:16:38,300 --> 00:16:39,600
You always add too much.

250
00:16:39,600 --> 00:16:42,900
I don't mind, but your dear grandson is building up his body.

251
00:16:42,900 --> 00:16:45,200
He can't eat too much salt.

252
00:16:45,200 --> 00:16:47,600
Stop it.

253
00:16:47,600 --> 00:16:51,200
