276
00:17:39,800 --> 00:17:41,700
- Okay.
- Try it on, Granny.

277
00:17:41,700 --> 00:17:44,400
Put it on later. Let's eat first.

278
00:17:44,400 --> 00:17:45,400
Sure.

279
00:17:45,400 --> 00:17:46,600
I'll try it on after the meal.

280
00:17:46,600 --> 00:17:48,600
Put it here, Granny.

281
00:17:57,800 --> 00:17:59,400
This is for you.

282
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:04,000
Even I get a gift?

283
00:18:04,000 --> 00:18:06,200
I know there's a better one, but it was too expensive.

284
00:18:06,200 --> 00:18:07,600
I just got the basic one.

285
00:18:07,600 --> 00:18:10,500
When I have the money, I'll buy you a better one.

286
00:18:10,500 --> 00:18:12,000
Stop thinking about money.

287
00:18:12,000 --> 00:18:14,800
Get into university first.

288
00:18:14,800 --> 00:18:19,200
What's with you? I got you a gift, but why didn't you thank me?

289
00:18:22,000 --> 00:18:24,800
Thank you. Your big brother loves it.

290
00:18:24,800 --> 00:18:26,400
What a sensible boy.

291
00:18:26,400 --> 00:18:28,300
Gross!

292
00:18:28,300 --> 00:18:30,000
Let's eat.

293
00:18:30,000 --> 00:18:33,700
In the future, you have to listen to your brother.

294
00:18:33,700 --> 00:18:36,000
Listen to him? No way.

295
00:18:36,000 --> 00:18:38,800
I bet I'll be more successful than you.

296
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:42,000
What an ambitious boy.

297
00:18:42,000 --> 00:18:43,600
That's ambitious?

298
00:18:43,600 --> 00:18:46,200
It's empty bragging.

299
00:18:46,200 --> 00:18:48,700
You can't even find a wife. You have no right to comment about me.

300
00:18:48,700 --> 00:18:51,300
When I graduate, I'll make sure to get a wife first.

301
00:18:51,300 --> 00:18:53,900
Granny, look at him. He's starting to daydream.

302
00:18:53,900 --> 00:18:56,400
Get a wife?

303
00:18:56,400 --> 00:18:59,800
How can you say that to your brother?

304
00:18:59,800 --> 00:19:02,600
Aren't you biased?

305
00:19:02,600 --> 00:19:04,200
Eat your food.

306
00:19:07,200 --> 00:19:09,000
Eat your eggs. We made them just for you.

307
00:19:09,000 --> 00:19:10,500
Got it.

308
00:19:13,400 --> 00:19:15,100
Is it tasty?

309
00:19:15,100 --> 00:19:16,400
Yeah, it's delicious.

