312
00:19:36,200 --> 00:19:42,800
♫ <i>The raindrops from the roof drip into my eyes quietly</i> ♫

313
00:19:42,800 --> 00:19:44,500
- Hongdou.
- Thank you.

314
00:19:44,500 --> 00:19:47,600
♫ <i>The world is like a quiet island</i> ♫

315
00:19:47,600 --> 00:19:50,700
Don't drop it. Get more for yourself later.

316
00:19:50,700 --> 00:19:52,600
Here we go.

317
00:19:53,300 --> 00:19:54,700
Mr. Ma.

318
00:19:54,700 --> 00:19:56,600
Mr. Hu, you're here.

319
00:19:56,600 --> 00:19:58,200
You sure came at the right time.

320
00:19:58,200 --> 00:20:00,500
We just finished cooking the meat and here you are.

321
00:20:01,600 --> 00:20:03,200
Thank you.

322
00:20:03,200 --> 00:20:05,000
Where's Xia Xia?

323
00:20:05,000 --> 00:20:07,500
He went to his master's place. We don't have to wait for him.

324
00:20:07,500 --> 00:20:10,100
By the way, Xia Xia brought back souvenirs from Shanghai.

325
00:20:10,100 --> 00:20:11,400
He can order these online.

326
00:20:11,400 --> 00:20:13,600
It's a hassle to bring them back.

327
00:20:13,600 --> 00:20:16,100
Let's eat while barbecuing. Everyone, eat up.

328
00:20:16,100 --> 00:20:18,000
Here, these can be eaten.

329
00:20:18,000 --> 00:20:19,600
Have the meat here.

330
00:20:19,600 --> 00:20:21,200
Don't spill it everywhere.

331
00:20:21,200 --> 00:20:24,300
It's a party. A party needs some good vibes.

332
00:20:27,400 --> 00:20:28,400
<i>Great!</i>

333
00:20:28,400 --> 00:20:30,600
- Who bought the flowers?
- Me.

334
00:20:30,600 --> 00:20:32,700
You have great taste.

335
00:20:32,700 --> 00:20:35,600
Enjoy my original composition later.

336
00:20:35,600 --> 00:20:37,200
"A Lonely Man."

337
00:20:37,200 --> 00:20:38,600
An original song.

338
00:20:38,600 --> 00:20:41,500
It's the perfect tune when drinking with friends.

339
00:20:42,940 --> 00:20:44,170
Here you go. Be careful.

340
00:20:44,170 --> 00:20:46,200
Okay.

341
00:20:46,200 --> 00:20:47,200
Here you go.

342
00:20:47,200 --> 00:20:48,600
- Hongdou.
- Thank you.

343
00:20:48,600 --> 00:20:50,800
- Use the large mug.
- We have more here.

344
00:20:50,800 --> 00:20:52,200
- Give it to your brother.
- He can't drink.

345
00:20:52,200 --> 00:20:54,600
He needs soemthing to drink! Drink this.

346
00:20:54,600 --> 00:20:56,100
Does everyone have a drink?

347
00:20:57,700 --> 00:20:59,400
Let's raise a toast!

348
00:20:59,400 --> 00:21:00,900
Hold on.

349
00:21:00,900 --> 00:21:03,600
Before we drink, we have to propose a toast.

350
00:21:03,600 --> 00:21:06,800
I'll start.

351
00:21:06,800 --> 00:21:09,600
I wish everyone great health and safety, yeah?

352
00:21:09,600 --> 00:21:10,800
Nice.

353
00:21:10,800 --> 00:21:14,400
I hope our friendship lasts forever.

354
00:21:14,400 --> 00:21:16,800
I wish everyone lasting happiness!

355
00:21:18,000 --> 00:21:20,600
As you hoist your sails to voyage in the vast sea,

356
00:21:20,600 --> 00:21:24,500
I hope you'll break through the storms and reach your goals.

357
00:21:24,500 --> 00:21:27,600
I hope everyone will get a windfall.

358
00:21:27,600 --> 00:21:29,800
May your wishes come true. Come on.

359
00:21:29,800 --> 00:21:32,000
May our country prosper!

360
00:21:32,000 --> 00:21:33,300
That's the best one today.

361
00:21:33,300 --> 00:21:34,600
She gets one more drink as a reward.

362
00:21:34,600 --> 00:21:38,000
May our country prosper!

363
00:21:38,000 --> 00:21:39,900
♫ <i>The light and shadows of the seasons</i> ♫

364
00:21:39,900 --> 00:21:42,400
♫ <i> I've seen the meteor that lights up the night sky</i> ♫

365
00:21:42,400 --> 00:21:43,800
Why is this champagne so sweet?

366
00:21:43,800 --> 00:21:45,600
- What's wrong?
- It's awful.

367
00:21:45,600 --> 00:21:49,600
♫ <i>When the wind rises, the sky will be cloudless</i> ♫

368
00:21:49,600 --> 00:21:51,800
Did you drink too much tea that champagne doesn't sit well with you?

369
00:21:51,800 --> 00:21:58,800
♫ <i>I'll head to a windy place to meet you</i> ♫

370
00:22:28,000 --> 00:22:29,400
Master.

371
00:22:38,600 --> 00:22:40,400
You're back.

372
00:22:43,200 --> 00:22:44,800
I got you a gift.

373
00:22:52,600 --> 00:22:54,000
Master.

374
00:22:54,800 --> 00:22:56,500
What else do you need to say?

375
00:22:58,800 --> 00:23:01,000
I'm not going to work in Shanghai.

376
00:23:01,000 --> 00:23:03,800
I still need your guidance and more practice.

377
00:23:07,910 --> 00:23:10,280
Master, did you hear me?

378
00:23:12,040 --> 00:23:14,020
I'm not deaf.

379
00:23:33,800 --> 00:23:34,990
What are you doing?

380
00:23:34,990 --> 00:23:36,660
Master, you always berate me for being lazy.

381
00:23:36,660 --> 00:23:39,770
I'll sweep the floor. Master, lift your feet.

382
00:23:41,050 --> 00:23:42,700
That's enough.

383
00:23:42,700 --> 00:23:44,410
Get lost.

384
00:23:44,910 --> 00:23:48,010
Master, please vent your anger by kicking me.

385
00:23:53,760 --> 00:23:55,730
I'm sorry, Master.

386
00:23:56,280 --> 00:23:58,280
I'll listen to you in the future.

387
00:23:58,280 --> 00:24:01,320
I won't play games or live stream.

388
00:24:02,280 --> 00:24:04,040
Will you still keep me as a disciple?

389
00:24:08,800 --> 00:24:11,750
You call me "Master."

390
00:24:11,750 --> 00:24:13,660
but what did I say?

391
00:24:15,280 --> 00:24:19,920
Stop pretending to work.

392
00:24:19,920 --> 00:24:23,340
You'll be distracted after a few days of hard work.

393
00:24:25,520 --> 00:24:27,080
Don't let your mind wander.

394
00:24:27,080 --> 00:24:28,810
Yes, Master!

395
00:24:28,810 --> 00:24:30,180
You scared me.

396
00:24:30,180 --> 00:24:31,700
Go and do your work.

397
00:24:31,700 --> 00:24:32,780
Leave.

398
00:24:32,780 --> 00:24:34,140
Do you want Palmiers?

399
00:24:34,140 --> 00:24:35,490
No.

400
00:24:35,490 --> 00:24:36,990
Do you know what they are?

401
00:24:36,990 --> 00:24:38,260
No clue.

402
00:24:39,490 --> 00:24:40,610
It's a Shanghai specialty.

403
00:24:40,610 --> 00:24:42,390
I don't want to eat it. You...

404
00:24:42,390 --> 00:24:43,240
Go away.

405
00:24:43,240 --> 00:24:45,010
It's delicious.

406
00:24:47,890 --> 00:24:48,610
What are you doing?

407
00:24:48,610 --> 00:24:51,860
- I...
- Have a bite.

408
00:24:54,080 --> 00:24:55,450
Is it nice?

409
00:24:56,120 --> 00:24:57,710
Not bad.

410
00:25:09,730 --> 00:25:11,130
When I was in high school,

411
00:25:11,130 --> 00:25:13,890
I wrote a love letter to a girl.

412
00:25:13,890 --> 00:25:16,750
In the end, she told our teacher.

413
00:25:16,750 --> 00:25:18,510
She said I was affecting her studies.

414
00:25:18,510 --> 00:25:22,040
The teacher was our form teacher who taught us Chinese.

415
00:25:22,040 --> 00:25:26,230
So, she read my letter aloud in class.

416
00:25:26,230 --> 00:25:30,220
She criticized my poor vocabulary and grammar mistakes.

417
00:25:30,220 --> 00:25:33,800
My love was too superficial.

418
00:25:33,800 --> 00:25:35,140
I bet she told your parents.

419
00:25:35,140 --> 00:25:37,090
She did, and my dad came over.

420
00:25:37,090 --> 00:25:39,370
But my dad didn't think much about this

421
00:25:39,370 --> 00:25:41,610
since I've always been a troublemaker.

422
00:25:41,610 --> 00:25:44,280
He just gave me one piece of advice.

423
00:25:44,280 --> 00:25:47,110
From now on, if you want to write a love letter,

424
00:25:47,110 --> 00:25:49,690
you must have the confidence to win her heart

425
00:25:49,690 --> 00:25:53,610
or you... you'll end up humiliating yourself.

426
00:25:54,800 --> 00:25:56,990
Your dad is an experienced man.

427
00:25:59,520 --> 00:26:01,090
Speaking of silly incidents,

428
00:26:01,090 --> 00:26:02,770
I have a story to tell.

429
00:26:02,770 --> 00:26:04,800
When I was in high school,

430
00:26:04,800 --> 00:26:09,370
I worked diligently to finish mock text papers once.

431
00:26:09,370 --> 00:26:13,020
When I took a break one day, I shot up to my feet...

432
00:26:14,360 --> 00:26:16,350
and felt my hemorrhoid burst.

433
00:26:16,350 --> 00:26:18,350
Oh my goodness!

434
00:26:19,070 --> 00:26:21,310
Even today,

435
00:26:21,310 --> 00:26:25,420
I can still remember the expression of the girl sitting beside me.

436
00:26:25,420 --> 00:26:26,850
My god.

437
00:26:26,850 --> 00:26:29,520
She even had a crush on me, but...

438
00:26:30,690 --> 00:26:32,510
All your stories aren't as horrible as mine.

439
00:26:32,510 --> 00:26:35,060
When I left the toilet in high school once,

440
00:26:35,060 --> 00:26:37,890
my dress was stuck in my underwear.

441
00:26:37,890 --> 00:26:39,110
Everyone saw my ass

442
00:26:39,110 --> 00:26:41,730
as I walked from the toilet all the way to the classroom.

443
00:26:41,730 --> 00:26:43,220
No one said a word to you?

444
00:26:43,220 --> 00:26:45,100
They were busy staring.

445
00:26:45,100 --> 00:26:49,140
I was overjoyed because I thought they were charmed by my beauty.

446
00:26:50,170 --> 00:26:52,170
Didn't you transfer schools?

447
00:26:52,170 --> 00:26:53,930
Nope.

448
00:26:53,930 --> 00:26:55,270
Didn't they laugh at you?

449
00:26:55,270 --> 00:26:56,410
They did.

450
00:26:56,410 --> 00:26:59,510
Tons of students come to our class to stare at me.

451
00:26:59,510 --> 00:27:01,240
I pretended I didn't give a damn,

452
00:27:01,240 --> 00:27:03,190
like nothing ever happened.

453
00:27:03,190 --> 00:27:05,010
What else could I do?

454
00:27:05,010 --> 00:27:07,550
Well, what happened after that?

455
00:27:07,550 --> 00:27:09,480
I don't really remember.

456
00:27:09,480 --> 00:27:11,450
I forgot about it as time passed.

457
00:27:14,010 --> 00:27:16,950
To be honest, this is just the spotlight effect.

458
00:27:16,950 --> 00:27:18,790
You always think you're in the spotlight,

459
00:27:18,790 --> 00:27:20,640
but no one really notices you.

460
00:27:20,640 --> 00:27:24,250
No matter how silly an incident is, it'll be forgotten in a few days.

461
00:27:24,970 --> 00:27:27,160
Tons of things happen in a day.

462
00:27:27,160 --> 00:27:29,150
It's impossible to remember everything.

463
00:27:29,150 --> 00:27:30,700
Yeah, that's right.

464
00:27:32,070 --> 00:27:34,190
When you're my age,

465
00:27:34,190 --> 00:27:37,320
you'll understand that suffering this level of humiliation

466
00:27:37,320 --> 00:27:42,120
is a blessing in life.

467
00:27:43,080 --> 00:27:46,680
You know, I fell in love with music when I was at university.

468
00:27:46,680 --> 00:27:48,400
So, I joined a band.

469
00:27:48,400 --> 00:27:52,820
After graduation, I didn't look for a job but practiced with the band.

470
00:27:52,820 --> 00:27:58,250
In the end, my dad was so angry that he had a stroke.

471
00:27:58,250 --> 00:28:03,440
Now, he can't walk well with just one leg.

472
00:28:07,150 --> 00:28:09,040
I'm plagued with regret.

473
00:28:09,040 --> 00:28:11,270
I'm too ashamed to go home.

474
00:28:17,210 --> 00:28:18,700
Yeah.

475
00:28:20,390 --> 00:28:22,490
We may see many people...

476
00:28:23,280 --> 00:28:28,390
building up success and basking in glory,

477
00:28:29,980 --> 00:28:32,360
but we also see them fall from great heights.

478
00:28:45,180 --> 00:28:46,690
A'Yuan,

479
00:28:47,410 --> 00:28:52,440
do you know that your brother paid for my university education?

480
00:28:52,440 --> 00:28:53,940
I know.

481
00:28:53,940 --> 00:28:56,740
Aunty Baoping blabbers about it so much that all of China probably knows by now.

482
00:28:57,490 --> 00:29:00,380
Why don't we know if everyone knows?

483
00:29:01,040 --> 00:29:03,360
My family was poor back then.

484
00:29:03,360 --> 00:29:05,550
We had no money for the tuition fees.

485
00:29:05,550 --> 00:29:07,700
My mom...

486
00:29:08,490 --> 00:29:11,120
went to borrow money from every other person around.

487
00:29:11,120 --> 00:29:15,310
At that time, I thought I should give up on university.

488
00:29:16,410 --> 00:29:19,090
It'd be better if I started working and earning money.

489
00:29:19,090 --> 00:29:21,480
My mom had to feed two kids by herself.

490
00:29:21,480 --> 00:29:27,420
Mom had to pay for our studies and keep us fed.

491
00:29:28,800 --> 00:29:31,080
It was tough for her.

492
00:29:31,870 --> 00:29:33,620
<i>Brother, have some tea.</i>

493
00:29:36,350 --> 00:29:40,020
<i>Xiaochun, your mom called me</i>

494
00:29:40,020 --> 00:29:43,380
<i>and said you want to quit school to work.</i>

495
00:29:47,360 --> 00:29:50,860
<i>Sister Honghong said the garment factory is recruiting.</i>

496
00:29:50,860 --> 00:29:53,390
<i>I can start with trimming threads if I work there.</i>

497
00:29:54,010 --> 00:29:56,070
<i>Well, do you want to continue with your studies?</i>

498
00:30:01,490 --> 00:30:04,310
<i>My wishes don't matter.</i>

499
00:30:04,310 --> 00:30:07,170
<i>You know how poor my family is.</i>

500
00:30:07,170 --> 00:30:10,490
<i>We depend on my mom for everything.</i>

501
00:30:13,800 --> 00:30:15,860
<i>Regardless,</i>

502
00:30:18,690 --> 00:30:23,190
<i>I can't... continue my studies.</i>

503
00:30:26,590 --> 00:30:28,750
<i>Let's leave money aside.</i>

504
00:30:28,750 --> 00:30:31,370
<i>Be frank with me.</i>

505
00:30:31,370 --> 00:30:33,970
<i>Do you want to pursue your studies?</i>

506
00:30:45,350 --> 00:30:50,190
<i>Aunty Baoping, I just started working and I don't have a high salary,</i>

507
00:30:50,190 --> 00:30:54,140
<i>but I can cover Xiaochun's tuition fees.</i>

508
00:30:55,250 --> 00:30:57,360
<i>Xiaochun is still young.</i>

509
00:30:57,360 --> 00:30:59,450
<i>She needs to study.</i>

510
00:31:01,070 --> 00:31:02,620
<i>Xiaochun,</i>

511
00:31:02,620 --> 00:31:05,130
<i>studying is never a waste of time.</i>

512
00:31:05,130 --> 00:31:08,900
<i>Knowledge is the bridge to the world.</i>

513
00:31:17,760 --> 00:31:19,920
At that time,

514
00:31:19,920 --> 00:31:23,050
A'Yao made a trip back from Beijing to speak to me.

